my husband was in the White House in the State

00:27:44.769 --> 00:27:51.289
Department; he worked for Kissinger. And I
just thought I was the leading generation

00:27:51.289 --> 00:27:57.139
of women that were starting to work; it never
occurred to me to have a career. And so, in

00:27:57.139 --> 00:28:01.549
my 20s, I wanted to grow up to be Jeffrey.
And when I hit 30, I thought, "He's great,

00:28:01.549 --> 00:28:02.860
but I don't wanna be him."

00:28:02.860 --> 00:28:04.190
[laughter]

00:28:04.190 --> 00:28:11.690
He's like the intellectual in the family.
I just wanna have fun. So, what I used to

00:28:11.690 --> 00:28:14.960
do when I wasn't working was have dinner parties
 -- every Saturday, I'd have a dinner party

00:28:14.960 --> 00:28:19.299
and I'd work my way through Julia Child's
"Mastering the Art of French Cooking", Volume

00:28:19.299 --> 00:28:23.230
I and Volume II, and I thought, "Well, maybe
I should be doing that instead." And I was

00:28:23.230 --> 00:28:27.649
sitting in my office in the White House, trying
to figure out what I wanted to be when I grew

00:28:27.649 --> 00:28:33.650
up and there was an ad for a specialty foods
store for sale. And I went home and I said

00:28:33.650 --> 00:28:36.759
to Jeffrey, "I gotta do something else." And
he said, "Well, pick something you think would

00:28:36.759 --> 00:28:40.630
be really fun. Pick something. Don't worry
about making money. Think about what you love

00:28:40.630 --> 00:28:44.940
to do because if you love it, you'll be really
good at it." And I said, "Funny you should

00:28:44.940 --> 00:28:45.940
mention it."

00:28:45.940 --> 00:28:46.940
[laughter]

00:28:46.940 --> 00:28:50.249
I saw this ad and bless his heart, he said,
"Let's go look at it tomorrow." So, I really

00:28:50.249 --> 00:28:54.749
had no idea what I was getting into, but I
knew I was going. The White House wasn't an

00:28:54.749 --> 00:29:00.289
